race.comment: THE KAMIKAZE (4) built on a nice second two starts back at this track with a win over 1000m at Townsville a week-and-a-half ago, getting home by a nose. Ivo Fry scored on him last time and retains the ride. Facing a tougher assignment but he is capable of running another bold race. SOWILO SIREN (8) was far from disgraced when second last start after being prominent at the bend over 1200m at Innisfail, beaten only a head. That followed a win here the start prior. Must raise the bar but another win is not out of the question. NORTHERNONTAP (5) has put together back-to-back placings, the latest when 1.75 lengths away in third over 1200m at Townsville when he was handy all the way. Has his share of ability and is hard to beat in this suitable race. YANKEE MISS (10) finished 11th over 1100m at Ballarat Synthetic at her most recent appearance on August 7. Has switched to the Steven Royes yard. Has found the right race and is worth including.
